# CLAUDE.md

## Project Overview

{{ project_name }} — Odoo {{ odoo_version }} development environment powered by Nix flakes.

## Environment

- **Python**: {{ python_version }} (managed by Nix, no virtualenv/pip — use `uv` for dependency management)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL {{ postgres_version }} — `{{ db_name }}` on `localhost:{{ postgres_port }}`, user/pass `{{ db_user }}/{{ db_password }}`
- **Odoo HTTP**: `localhost:{{ odoo_http_port }}`, {% if odoo_major | int >= 17 %}gevent{% else %}longpolling{% endif %} `localhost:{{ odoo_gevent_port }}`, nginx proxy `localhost:{{ nginx_port }}`
- **Odoo credentials**: `admin` / `admin`
- **Config**: `odoo.conf` (generated) | **Logs**: `odoo.log` (rotated daily)

## Key Commands

```bash
# Services
systemctl --user {start|stop|restart|status} odoo.service postgres.service nginx.service

# Update/install module (stop running odoo first)
odoo -c ${{ project_dir_var }}/odoo.conf -u module_name --workers 0 --stop-after-init --logfile=/dev/stdout

# Interactive shell
odoo shell -c ${{ project_dir_var }}/odoo.conf --workers 0 --stop-after-init

# Run a specific test class/method
odoo -c ${{ project_dir_var }}/odoo.conf -u module_name --workers 0 --test-enable --test-tags module_name.test_file_name --stop-after-init --logfile=/dev/stdout

# Clone/update repos and regenerate addon symlinks
nix run .#update-repos
```

## Architecture

```
src/
├── odoo/                  # Odoo {{ odoo_version }} CE source (read-only, branch {{ odoo_version }})
{% if custom_repo_name %}
├── {{ custom_repo_name }}/   # Custom modules — this is where we develop
{% endif %}
└── ...                    # Third-party repos from addons.yaml (read-only)
```

{% if custom_repo_name %}
- **Custom modules** live in `src/{{ custom_repo_name }}/` (prefix `{{ module_prefix }}_*`)
{% endif %}
- **Third-party repos** are pinned in `addons.yaml`
- **Addon symlinks** are managed at `.local/share/Odoo/addons/{{ odoo_version }}/` by `nix run .#update-repos`
- Never edit OCA/core code under `src/` (enforced by the guard-readonly hook){% if custom_repo_name %} — extend via a `{{ module_prefix }}_*` module{% endif %}
